The police at Villa Nora outside Lephalale are investigating a case of culpable homicide after five people lost their lives in bakkie rollover crash on Friday. It is alleged that twenty-six (26) people were loaded in an open Toyota bakkie when the driver lost control along the R518 road next to Shongoane 1 and vehicle crashed. According to the police, the people were on their way to a church service at Marapong outside Lephalale when the crash happened. Three people died instantly and two succumbed to injuries on arrival at Lephalale District hospital. The names of the deceased will be made known once the next-of-kin have been notified. The cause of the accident is not known. -TNA Reporter